						               													<description>Diagonal Blocks is an abstract strategy game modeled after Blokus, and playable with a Blokus set.  The pieces, (same as Blokus) consist of a complete set of all polyominoes up to size 5.  The board is 20x20 (smaller in 2 or 3 player variants) with the six squares nearest each corner removed.  Play begins at a starting square for each player, and each players subsequent move must contact his previously placed pieces only at a diagonal points.   The game ends when no further pieces can be played.  The winner is the player who covered the most squares with his pieces.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Vis-a-vis Blokus, the differences are:&amp;#10;(1) The corners are removed from the board so there are barely more squares on the board than pieces to be played.&amp;#10;(2) There are no special scoring bonuses. The count of squares covered is the entire score.&amp;#10;(3) In two player variants, A &amp;quot;swap&amp;quot; rule applies to the second move.   This removes the first player advantage.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Variations:&amp;#10; Diagonal Blocks (3 player, intermediate size board)&amp;#10; Diagonal Blocks Duo (2 player)&amp;#10; Diagonal Blocks Classic (2 player, 4 color)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Online Play&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Boardspace.net real-time, AI option&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Mobile Apps&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Boardspace.net local multiplayer or online, IOS&amp;#10;     Boardspace.net local multiplayer or online, Android&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
